RESOURCE
  Show mineral and terrain resources for owned sectors.

SYNTAX
  resource [<sects>]
  reso     [<sects>]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays natural resource values for each owned sector.  These
  are fixed terrain properties that determine what a sector can
  produce when designated appropriately.

  Column meanings:
    sect      - x,y and designation
    min       - mineral density  (iron mines use this)
    gold      - gold deposit     (gold mines use this)
    fert      - fertility        (agribusiness sectors use this)
    ocontent  - oil content      (oil fields use this)
    uran      - uranium content  (uranium mines use this)

  Values range 0-100.  A value of 0 means that resource cannot be
  extracted regardless of designation.  Use this to pick the best
  location before designating new production sectors.

EXAMPLE
  resource *                check all sectors
  resource -5:5,-5:5        find good sites near capital

SEE ALSO
  census  designate  sector-types  show
